<th>Radioactivity</th>
<th>Absorbed Dose</th>
<th>Dose Equivalent</th>
<th>Exposure</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Common Units</td>
<td>curie (Ci)</td>
<td>rad</td>
<td>rem</td>
<td>roentgen (R)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>SI Units</td>
<td>becquerel (Bq)</td>
<td>gray (Gy)</td>
<td>sievert (Sv)</td>
<td>coulomb/kilogram (C/kg)</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>Following is a list of prefixes and their meanings that are often used i=
n conjunction with SI units:</p>
